title: High Terrestrial Conservation Efforts
description: In 2024, Seychelles dedicated 68.1% of its total land area to terrestrial protected areas, showcasing a strong commitment to environmental conservation.

title: Universal Newborn Tetanus Protection
description: By 2023, Seychelles achieved a 100% rate of newborns protected against tetanus, ensuring comprehensive healthcare for its youngest citizens.

title: Minimal Aquaculture Production
description: In 2017, Seychelles reported an aquaculture production of just 0.1 metric tons, indicating a limited focus or capacity in this sector.

title: Low Net Bilateral Aid from Sweden
description: In 2017, Seychelles received a minimal net bilateral aid flow of approximately $10,000 from Sweden, reflecting limited financial support from this donor.

title: Limited Official Aid Received
description: In 2021, Seychelles received $50,000 in net official aid, suggesting a relatively low level of international financial assistance.
